enum NotesN

Natural notes names. 's' means sharp, e.g. Ds is D# The central octave is the fourth, thus C4 is the "central C"

enum NotesP

void play_song ( Song *  s  ) 

Plays a song using busy-waiting 

  usage example:
  Note notes[] = {{Sol6, 100}, {Mi6,50}, {Sol6, 50}, {Mi6, 25}}; 
  Song s = { sizeof(notes)/sizeof(Note), 10, notes};
  play_song(&s);

Variable Documentation

float notes_frequency[]

Notes frequencies, in Hz, synchronized with arrays NotesN and NotesP. E.G. frequency[Do5] is the frequency of a central Do, 261.63Hz

NOTICE: this array is NOT defined in this header file, as variables should not be declared in header files. You have to copy/paste it to a source file (*.c).
